value: Bred, formerly, from Mackenzie east to Hudson Bay and south to Nebraska and Iowa; now breeds only in a few localities in southern Mackenzie and northern Saskatchewan. Wintered, formerly, from the Gulf States to central Mexico; now winters exclusively in southeastern Texas.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Open, marshy coniferous woods with shallow lakes and ponds; formerly also fresh-water marshes and wet prairies; in winter, primarily fresh-water and brackish marshes.
br freshwater marshes & sloughs around potholes and lake margins & in wet parairies of wilderness wetlands;winters coastal brackish wetlands.Wild population 183 in 1998
